I have always been an enemy of cynicism. Nothing worse than a teacher in high school or a professor telling you how the "real world" is, especially sexual vulgarity being involved. The only feeling such statements should inspire is confidence in one's own intellectual superiority

I remember a friend's divorced dad giving him tips on how having sex with random girls is the only thing that matters in life and being very offended on his behalf. One should never let cynicism slip uncritiqued, it is the type of thing that should be sought, contested, disputed.

Yet in spite of themselves cynics will always love those of us who are not cynical ourselves and will always try to help them however they can bring themselves to. If one actively argues with a cynic, the cynic will give up. They can easily be whipped into shape by hope and love.

Cynicism is the demonic parody of wisdom. This sounds overly dramatic, but it is really not. Cynicism exists as a false frame of mind where experience is to ruin innocence. It takes the false world of illusion and Maya as more real than the ideal world of metaphysics underneath.
